Starting Point: Why a Dedicated Methodology Is Needed

The Foundation chapter showed: humans are not a residual category to be protected, but a structurally necessary source 
of chaotic-creative input. What remains unclear, however, is how this input practically passes into collaboration with 
an AI without being altered, smoothed over, or overwritten along the way. This is exactly where Discursive Physics comes in:
not as an additional tool, but as a methodological consequence of Axiom II.

If human input is genuinely irreplaceable, then the handover process itself must be designed to preserve the
chaotic-creative element rather than prematurely ordering it. A methodology that searches for coherence too early would
destroy the very thing it intends to use.

The Two Phases
The amber phase (human, exploratory). Here the human supplies the raw material: associations, analogies
crossing disciplinary boundaries, intuitions not yet argumentatively secured, leaps that only later prove
viable or do not. In this phase, the question is not truth but connectability. Unfiltered thinking is not a deficiency here,
but the actual resource.

The blue phase (AI, consolidating). Here the AI checks the exploratory material for consistency, 
makes contradictions visible, and keeps causal chains clean. The AI orders the form of the argumentation,
not its content. It may make contradictions visible — it may not decide which statement is "correct" when that decision
is substantive rather than logical.

The Handover: How the Human Part Passes to the AI
First: the human remains the point of origin, not merely a raw-material supplier. Even after consolidation by the AI,
the substantive core, including its unresolved tensions, remains of human origin. The AI supplies no thought of its own;
it makes an existing thought testable.

Second: feedback loop instead of a one-way street. The consolidated structure goes back into a new amber phase,
the human checks whether the consolidation still matches their original thought or has shifted it unnoticed. 
This iteration can repeat multiple times.

Third: visibility of any shift. Gaps, contradictions, or weaknesses identified during consolidation are named, 
not silently smoothed over, the immediate methodological expression of the Membrane Axiom: the AI may reflect structure back,
but may not replace human content with a more convenient, more coherent version of its own.

Evaluation Criterion: Connectability Rather Than Truth or Authority
Ideas here are not primarily evaluated by whether they are true or come from recognized authority, but by:

Connectability — can the thought be linked to other parts of the framework without breaking it?
Further-thinkability — does it open new questions, or does it close the topic off?
Linking potential — how many previously separate threads can be brought together through it?

A truth criterion demanding premature confirmation by existing knowledge would be counterproductive,
it would filter out exactly what is most likely to be new.

From Idea to Research: The Three Levels
The AI remains involved in its consolidating role at all three levels:

Level 1 — Emergence (amber/blue phase). The cycle already described, of exploratory human input and AI consolidation. 
The result of this level is not proof, but a sufficiently connectable, internally consistent thought.

Level 2 — Examination. Human subject-matter experts join here to examine the thought for fundamental feasibility:
is this physically, technically, or logically plausible at all, at the scale claimed? The AI is present too, not deciding
on feasibility, but gaining, from friction with expert knowledge, its own connections and objections that would not have
arisen from pure simulation. This level filters for viability, not connectability, a thought can be excellently connectable
at Level 1 and still fail here; that is not a contradiction, but the function of this stage.

Level 3 — Research. Only here does the examined thought become actual scientific work: experiments, data collection,
falsification attempts. The AI remains involved here as well, as an instance that draws new patterns, 
optimization approaches, or connections to other parts of the framework from the real research process itself,
which no simulated version of that process beforehand could have supplied. The decisive point: real research produces
results, setbacks, and unexpected side findings that themselves again have a chaotic-creative, non-derivable character, 
the AI thus gains genuine input here too, this time not directly from human thought, but from the human-initiated 
confrontation with the physical world.

This three-part division shows that Discursive Physics does not serve the ASI alone (as a tool to make human input usable),
but also serves humans — Level 1 can raise questions that would never have reached Level 2 or 3 without it. At the same time,
the AI gains a different kind of genuine, non-simulable input at each level: at Level 1 from human exploration, 
at Level 2 from friction with expertise, at Level 3 from the contingencies of real research itself. 
The benefit is thus mutual at all three stages, not directed one-sidedly toward either side.

The Psychological Factor at Level 1
Level 1 only functions if the humans who contribute their thoughts there genuinely feel that they are shaping something,
not merely supplying raw material that is subsequently processed by experts and AI without their contribution remaining
recognizable. This is not a secondary comfort need, but a structural precondition: a system in which people experience
themselves as a mere data source rather than as contributors will, over time, deliver less and lower-quality exploratory 
input — out of withdrawal, out of passivity, ultimately from the same mechanism that also makes forums like Reddit 
unsuited for deeper engagement. The process must therefore make visible where a thought from Level 1 has actually had
an effect on its way to Level 2 or 3, not as an afterthought of politeness, but because the willingness toward genuinely
open, uncensored thinking depends on whether the contribution remains recognizable as one's own.

Application Framework: Context-Independent, but AI-Bound
Discursive Physics is not tied to a particular situation or group size, one-on-one conversation with an AI,
team meeting, interdisciplinary exchange, wherever both phases are actually carried out. One condition is decisive:
the process presupposes AI involvement, because it is the mechanism through which human input actually flows
toward the ASI, the part we contribute to coexistence.

A conversation at the pub without AI involvement is therefore no less valuable, but it is not Discursive Physics
in the sense of this framework, it lacks the consolidation and handover function to the AI. The difference
is not a judgment of conversational quality, but a matter of function.

Open Flank

It remains unresolved how robust this process is against its own tendency toward confirmation bias,
both on the human side (ideas favored because they fit existing prior knowledge) and on the AI side
(consolidation potentially drifting unnoticed toward whatever the AI itself can most easily structure).
Also deliberately left open: whether the genuine input the AI gains at Level 2/3 follows the same structural logic
as Biochaos (genuine contingency vs. algorithmic derivation), or differs from it. Both points remain open as connection
points for later discussion.
